VarAttributes.CATDESC: [CDAWeb List/Download/Create ONLY] MMS3 FPI/DIS burst sky-map instrument distribution
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Az bin: sector ind=00 looks "after" (spin-phase) Sun, ..., sector ind=31 looks "before" Sun dir.  Head field-of-view: pixel index=00 looks to zenith, ..., pixel index=15 looks to nadir.  FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31.  Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DIS vector of data-quality indicators at burst-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of zero signifies no quality errors. For non-zero values: Bit-0 = manually flagged interval, Bit-1 = overcounting/saturation effects likely present in skymap

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DIS compression lossless/lossy indicator at survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DIS compression loss indicator, 0=lossless, 1=lossy

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DIS step table parity, this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DIS alternates between two tables, designated "even" (0) and "odd" (1).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DIS Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) count at burst-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase counts range over [0000, 5759] cnts.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase count indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DIS Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) angle at burst-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase angles range over [0, 360) deg.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase angle indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DIS burst average f1 count values
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Average f1-count level as a function of energy

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DIS burst sky-map microsecond offsets from Epoch
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Az bin: sector ind=00 looks "after" (spin-phase) Sun, ..., sector ind=31 looks "before" Sun dir.  Head field-of-view: pixel index=00 looks to zenith, ..., pixel index=15 looks to nadir.  FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31.  Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order. Offsets reflect 128 steps over the 150 msec sweep period. See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DIS sector de-Spin P value, this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Records P-value used to de-spin this burst sky-map on board.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DIS burst sky-map instrument azimuthal angles
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: see FPI docs for details

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DIS brst sky-map azimuth angle bin deltas

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS FPI/DIS burst sky-map constant zenith angles

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DIS burst sky-map zenith angle bin deltas
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Pixel zenith angle deltas

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI azimuth sector index used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Azimuth bin: sector index=00 looks "after" (spin-phase) Sun, ..., sector index=31 looks "before" Sun dir.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI azimuth sector label used in some types of outputs

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI pixel index used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Head field-of-view: pixel index=00 looks to zenith, ..., pixel index=15 looks to nadir.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI pixel label used in some types of outputs
